```

### Step 2: Enhance the CSS

In the `styles.css`, we can add more styles for a better look, feel, and responsiveness. Also, we'll include styles for a progress bar and tweak the design to be more engaging.

```css
/* Add these styles to the existing ones */

body {
    background-color: #eee;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 20px;
    font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
}

.quiz-container {
    background-color: white;
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 20px;
    margin: auto;
    max-width: 600px;
}

ul li label {
    cursor: pointer;
}

/* Responsive design */
@media (max-width: 600px) {
    .quiz-container {
        width: 90%;
        padding: 15px;
    }
}

.progress-bar {
    background-color: #e0e0e0;
    border-radius: 20px;
    padding: 3px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
}

.progress {
    background-color: #4caf50;
    border-radius: 20px;
    height: 20px;
    width: 0%;
    text-align: center;
    color: white;
    transition: width 0.4s ease;
}

.timer {
    text-align: right;
}
```

### Step 3: Updating the JavaScript with Timer and Progress Bar

Enhance your `script.js` by implementing a simple timer for the entire quiz duration and a progress indication for visual feedback.

```javascript
// Keep the initial quiz setup as is, and add the following enhancements

let time = 120; // Total quiz time in seconds

const progressBar = document.createElement('div');
progressBar.classList.add('progress-bar');
const progress = document.createElement('div');
progress.classList.add('progress');
const timerEl = document.createElement('div');
timerEl.classList.add('timer');
quiz.insertBefore(progressBar, quiz.firstChild);
progressBar.appendChild(progress);
quiz.insertBefore(timerEl, progressBar);

const updateProgress = () => {
    let progressPercentage = ((currentQuiz / quizData.length) * 100).toString();
    progress.style.width = `${progressPercentage}%`;
    progress.innerText = `Question ${currentQuiz + 1} of ${quizData.length}`;
};

const updateTime = () => {
    timerEl.innerText = `Time left: ${time}s`;
    time--;
    if (time < 0) {
        // End quiz if time runs out
        endQuiz();
    }
};

let timer = setInterval(updateTime, 1000);

function endQuiz() {
    clearInterval(timer);
    quiz.innerHTML = `<h2>You answered correctly at ${score}/${quizData.length} questions.</h2>
    <button onclick="location.reload()">Retry</button>`;
    // Add the pass/fail message based on score criteria
    const passFailText = score >= (70 / 120) * quizData.length ? "You Passed!" : "You Failed!";
    quiz.innerHTML += `<h3>${passFailText}</h3>`;
}

submitBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
    // Modify the event listener to include updateProgress call
    const answer = getSelected();
    if (answer) {
        if (answer === quizData[currentQuiz].correct) {
            score++;
        }
        currentQuiz++;
        if (currentQuiz < quizData.length) {
            updateProgress(); // Update the progress bar each time a new question is loaded
            loadQuiz();
        } else {
            endQuiz();
        }
    }
});
```

### Enhancements Explanation

- **Progress Bar**: We've added a progress bar on top of the questions which visually indicates how many questions have been completed and how many are left.
- **Timer Feature**: A simple countdown timer was added, starting with 120 seconds for the entire quiz. When the time runs out, the quiz ends regardless of how many questions were answered. This encourages quicker thinking and adds a layer of challenge.
- **Responsive Design**: Additional CSS media queries ensure the quiz looks good on both desktop and mobile devices.
- **End Quiz on Timer End**: When the timer runs out, the quiz will automatically end, showing the final score and a message to the user.

This enhanced version of the quiz app provides a more engaging user experience with visual feedback through a progress bar, a challenging element with a countdown timer, and responsiveness for various device sizes. It can be further expanded with features such as question shuffling, category selection, and even incorporating a backend to save user scores or progress.
